op align=left class=m><span class=title> I've cast my last spell...</span><hr size=1> I have come to the end of my patience, and the end of my desire to play this game.  Please understand, this is meant in no way to reflect on the people I have met and friend I have made.<br>
<br>
My decision comes from many different factors:<br>
<br>
1.  Difficulty in finding a group.  75% of the time I end up soloing, like so many other wizards under the level needed for planes raids (necessary Lure spells) or other “uber” encounters.  <br>
2.  The insane downtime (oh well, let me sit here and watch my screen for 10 or 12 minutes waiting for the blue bar to come back…  play gems, fold clothes, or go watch TV?  Hmmmm… what to do…  at this rate I could maybe get 6 kills an hour…wow...)<br>
3.  The high penalty and time drain for death.<br>
4.  Verant Interactive's pathetic excuse for Customer Support.<br>
5.  I don’t want to be a “Master of Transportation”.  I want to be a Wizard.  <br>
<br>
Some have said, &quot;Wait for Luclin!&quot;  No... not worth it.  I remmber similar comments about Kunark and Velious.  It's still going to be run by the same people.  They are going to continue to make the same mistakes.  <br>
<br>
It's no longer fun for me.  It stopped being a game and turned into a monotonous, time consuming, frustrating part of my life.  <br>
<br>
BUT, bearing all that in mind, I still have lots of fond memories. .To all you that helped me when I needed it, to all you that laughed at my jokes, and answered my posts...<br>
<br>
THANK YOU!<br>
<br>
I wish you all the best.  <br>
<br>
Personally, I'm looking forward to a game that's not run by Verant Interactive.<br>
<br>
Macksin<br>
